The Xxxxxxxxx Xxxxx Xxxxxxxx Xxxxxx (ILRC) uses policy advocacy, capacity building, and civic engagement strategies to help immigrant families be together and thrive. Through our efforts, immigrants can more easily obtain green cards, United States citizenship, permission to stay and work in the United States, and protection from deportation. As a national nonprofit resource center, we provide immigration legal trainings, technical assistance, and legal educational materials, as well as engage in advocacy and immigrant civic participation, outreach, and education to advance immigrant rights. The ILRC is headquartered in San Francisco and has offices in California's Central Valley, San Antonio & Austin, Texas, and Washington DC.

The ILRC was founded in 1979 by Professor Bill Ong Hing who recognized an unfulfilled need for legal services to represent immigrant clients and to supply legal advice to community-based and legal services organizations. Since then, the mission of the ILRC has been to work with and educate immigrants, community organizations, and the legal sector to continue to build a democratic society that values diversity and the rights of all people.

data.long_description:
Xxxxxxx Xxxxxxxx Xxxxxx (TCT) started out in 2007 with a staff of four and a vision of being a small "lifestyle" company, one that would allow a handful of employees to provide dedicated service to clients while supporting their families. During those early days, working off of folding tables in a historic house converted into office space, our founding partners didn't anticipate the growth and evolution to come.
As our firm recently celebrated our 11-year anniversary, we've transitioned from that little lifestyle business to a firm with over 30 employees and offices in New York and Washington, DC. Our vision today is to become and remain a "small giant," a client-focused, boutique cost estimating firm of choice whose ownership and leadership can be passed on from generation to generation.
We're large enough to work on exciting projects with renowned firms, but small enough to ensure that design teams can achieve excellence and projects can be built. Our cost estimates have helped architects and engineers construct parks and recreation centers, rehabilitate properties damaged by Superstorm Sandy, renovate schools, and build new embassies overseas. The results of our work can be seen in iconic locations ranging from the Javits Convention Center to the U.S. Capitol Building.

Our offices are located in New York, NY; Huntington, NY; and Washington, DC.

data.name: Xxxxxxxx
data.long_description:
Xxxxxxxx is a medical diagnostics company focused on providing a more rapid and insightful way to diagnose fast-moving and immune-mediated diseases. Our FDA cleared IntelliSep test is pioneering a new way of quickly and accurately analyzing white blood cells to stratify a patient’s risk of sepsis by performing a biomechanical evaluation of white blood cells collected from a standard blood draw in under 10 minutes. 

Xxxxxxxx’s first market application will be for sepsis, one of the fastest-moving, most lethal conditions in the world. Sepsis, a dysregulated immune response to infection, is often difficult to quickly and accurately diagnose. Sepsis is the no. 1 cause of death in hospitals, taking the lives of 270,000 people every year in the U.S. – more than opioid overdoses, prostate cancer, and breast cancer combined.  Mortality from sepsis increases as much as eight percent with every hour of delayed treatment, and as much as 80 percent of sepsis deaths could be prevented with rapid diagnosis and treatment, making early detection essential. 
Xxxxxxxx aims to provide critical insight for early identification of patients at risk of having sepsis, in the time needed for it to be useful.

Follow us on Twitter: twitter.com/Xxxxxxxx
data.seo_description: At Xxxxxxxx, we’re focused on more rapid and insightful ways to diagnose fast-moving and immune-mediated diseases.

data.name: Xxxxx Xxxxxxx
data.long_description:
What if we opened our minds to a new type of philanthropy?
 
One that opens doors for nonprofits to better resources and bigger networks, instead of donors just opening their wallets.

One that opens the space for nonprofits to collaborate together and share their experiences, as opposed to working alone and straining their limited resources.

One that's open to listening to what nonprofits have to say, rather than telling them what they have to do.

One that's open to long-term partnerships more than yearly program support.

A new type of philanthropy, that's open to investing in a vision over insisting on immediate results.

This might sound like magical thinking, but it's why we created Xxxxx Xxxxxxx.

Over the past 10 years, we've watched and worked closely with nonprofits to identify how they work best in today's world. This first-hand experience has given us a clear vision of how to reimagine philanthropy to help nonprofits effectively change and impact their community. First, through funding long-term, capacity-building grants; then, fostering collaboration between nonprofits; and finally, empowering donors to use their curiosity and creativity to help a nonprofit thrive.

Now, we want everyone in the nonprofit community to profit from our experience.

By helping individual and institutional donors recognize the way they give is just as important as the amount they give when it comes to making the most of their efforts.

By providing more nonprofits with the organizational resources & relationships they need today, so they can realize their full potential—and impact—tomorrow.

By showing the world how we can make a bigger difference in people's lives when we're open to a different type of philanthropy.

Xxxxx Xxxxxxx | Opening up new paths for philanthropy.

data.long_description:
XxXxxxxx is a nimble digital agency made up of senior talent with big-agency experience and a desire for a more holistic, human approach to digital and technology projects.

Since XxXxxxxx launched in 2017, we've tackled our Clients' complex business challenges. Our team is passionate about connecting dots and helping to uncover the unknown. Why are we designing and developing mobile apps? What are the business implications and goals for your paid media campaign? How does it all work together now, and how about 5 years from now? The XxXxxxxx team is going to ask questions. A lot of them. Aligning early and often with Clients is step-one in ensuring a successful and pain-free project.

Our team size and structure are as much a part of our strategic toolkit as how we approach individual projects. Every Client deserves the detailed and focused approach often reserved for only ‘top' Clients at bigger firms. We take a fine-dining approach to Client relationships. Every touchpoint has purpose, is planned, and needs to be executed with even the littlest details in mind.

It's because all of our team members have deep experience that this approach works. Each is empowered with the autonomy to make impactful decisions and be Client-facing resources. This autonomy and access makes projects move faster with an agility to continuously align with ever-evolving business objectives.

We're here to break down your business challenges, and build a new kind of experience for your customers, partners, influencers, members and users. An experience focused on real objectives and tangible outcomes. We do all of this with a consistent approach, delivered with customized support for every Client.
